<div id="review_4349197307" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4349197307" />
    <a title="Catherine" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/28248440-catherine"><img alt="Catherine" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1585884650p2/28248440.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4349197307?book_show_action=true">Nov 27, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Catherine" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Catherine" href="/user/show/28248440-catherine">Catherine</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781908518248" href="/book/show/32198764-siege-at-jadotville">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4349197307" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3551129604779021493">This book honestly should probably receive a 3.5-star rating, however I&apos;m sticking with 3-stars because I did find this novel difficult to get into at times. If I&apos;m totally honest, I think you&apos;d be better off watching the Netflix movie as it does a good job of focusing on the siege itself and the men involved. That being said, I did enjoy the fact that this went above and beyond that to put into perspective the scope of just how dire the situation was at the time not just for A Company, but for </span>
  <span id="freeText3551129604779021493" style="display:none">This book honestly should probably receive a 3.5-star rating, however I'm sticking with 3-stars because I did find this novel difficult to get into at times. If I'm totally honest, I think you'd be better off watching the Netflix movie as it does a good job of focusing on the siege itself and the men involved. That being said, I did enjoy the fact that this went above and beyond that to put into perspective the scope of just how dire the situation was at the time not just for A Company, but for the troops involved in trying to aid them as well. <br />Overall, if you're thinking of reading it I'd say go for it, but don't expect it to be an easy read unless you understand military abbreviations.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3551129604779021493" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
