  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4481635889" />
    <a title="Jeremias Urieta" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/106582031-jeremias-urieta"><img alt="Jeremias Urieta" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4481635889?book_show_action=true">Jan 16, 2022</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jeremias Urieta" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jeremias Urieta" href="/user/show/106582031-jeremias-urieta">Jeremias Urieta</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781908518248" href="/book/show/32198764-siege-at-jadotville">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4481635889" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6329610096393969628">This book is ideal for the people who have seen the film. The author focuses the big picture and all the agents that were involved in the conflict, even outside the battlefield. If the reader has not seen the film, the book can become a difficult read at times. Apart from this you&apos;ll be presented to a consistent historical acount backed by great sources. Overall, it is a good book!</span>
  <span id="freeText6329610096393969628" style="display:none">This book is ideal for the people who have seen the film. The author focuses the big picture and all the agents that were involved in the conflict, even outside the battlefield. If the reader has not seen the film, the book can become a difficult read at times. Apart from this you'll be presented to a consistent historical acount backed by great sources. Overall, it is a good book!</span>
